<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n09152g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09152g">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09152g"> 152(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ = please <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n09152g"> <li>FW unlocated</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Fancy a mother so anxious to say &ldquo;please&rdquo; to her child that she calls him &ldquo;Father&rdquo; as an <mark>equivalent for &ldquo;please,&rdquo;</mark> then puts it all in the subjunctive mood to soften off her maternal request for some small service he renders her. <small> Dan Crawford, <a name="BTLG1" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#BTLG1"><cite title="source">Back to the Long Grass</cite></a> (1923) 108</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
